P(A|B \cup C) = P(A)
A
 B \cup C
P(A|B \cap C)=P(A)
A
B \cap C
A
A
B \cup C = V, B \cap C= W
W \subset V
P(A|W)=P(A)
P(A|W)=P(A|V)=\frac{P(A|V)P(V)}{P(V)} \Leftrightarrow P(A|W)P(V)=P(A|V)P(V)=P(A \cap V)
W=V.
P(V) \geq P(W)
P(A|W)P(V) \geq P(A)|W)P(W)=P(A \cap W)
P(A \cap V) \geq P(A \cap W)
V=W
\Omega
P(A \mid A \cup \Omega) = P(A)
P(A \mid A \cap \Omega) = 1
